--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This role manages openntpd.

The ntpd daemon implements the Simple Network Time Protocol version 4 as
described in RFC 2030 and the Network Time Protocol version 3 as described in
RFC 1305. It can synchronize the local clock to one or more remote NTP servers
and act as NTP server itself, redistributing the local time.

For more detailed information on the usage and available configuration options
please consult the following sections.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
USAGE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: openntpd
       openntpd_state: 'install'

ENABLE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: openntpd
       openntpd_state: 'enable'
       openntpd_server: ['ntp01.domain.tld', 'ntp02.domain.tld']

DISABLE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: openntpd
       openntpd_state: 'disable'
       openntpd_server: ['ntp01.domain.tld', 'ntp02.domain.tld']

REMOVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: openntpd
       openntpd_state: 'remove'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
VARIABLES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ROLE
  openntpd_state
    Description: Control the state of the role.
    Implemented: 0.1
    Required   : False
    Value      : Predetermined
    Type       : String
    Default    : 'enable'
    Options    :
      Install: 'true' | 'yes' | 'install'
      Enable : 'start' | 'on' | 'enable'
      Disable: 'stop' | 'off' | 'disable'
      Remove : 'false' | 'no' | 'remove'

  openntpd_listen
    Description: Define the 'openntpd_listen' option.
    Implemented: 0.1
    Required   : False
    Value      : Arbitrary
    Type       : Array
    Default    : []
    Options    :
      Examples: ['*'] | ['127.0.0.1', '::1'] | ['192.168.1.10']
      None    : []

  openntpd_ntpd_conf_template
    Description: Define the template source for 'ntpd.conf.j2'.
                 Any value other than "{{ansible_os_family}}" requires a Jinja2
                 file to be created. The custom Jinja2 file for an example
                 configuration called 'example' needs to be placed as follows:
                 'openntpd/templates/example/ntpd.conf.j2'
    Implemented: 0.1
    Required   : False
    Value      : Arbitrary
    Type       : String
    Default    : "{{ansible_os_family}}"
    Options    :
      Examples: 'example' | 'environment' | 'hostname'

  openntpd_server
    Description: Define the 'openntpd_server' option.
    Implemented: 0.1
    Required   : False
    Value      : Arbitrary
    Type       : Array
    Default    : ["ntp.{{ansible_domain}}"]
    Options    :
      Examples: ['ntp.domain.tld'] | ['ntp01.domain.tld', 'ntp02.domain.tld'] |
                ['ntp01.domain.tld', 'ntp02.domain.tld', 'ntp03.domain.tld']
      None    : []

  openntpd_servers
    Description: Define the 'openntpd_servers' option.
    Implemented: 0.1
    Required   : False
    Value      : Arbitrary
    Type       : Array
    Default    : []
    Options    :
      Examples: ['pool.domain.tld'] |
                ['pool.domain01.tld', 'pool.domain02.tld'] |
                ['pool.domain01.tld', 'pool.domain02.tld', 'pool.domain03.tld']
      None    : []

